It tells the story of Matt McGregor (Andrew Clarke), one of the richest and most influential man in town, as well as widower father of three children: Colin(Brett Climo), who's the town preacher, Rob (Guy Pearce) and Danni (Joelene Crnogorac/Kristie Raymond), the tomboy youngest daughter. Unresolved sexual tension comes in the shape of Matt's childhood independent, free-spirited friend, the recently widowed Kathleen O'Neil (Wendy Hughes), who's returned to Paterson's Ridge with her son after having spent many years in England.
